## Proposed Changes

We will generate a new Vite + React project and configure Tailwind CSS:

### Foundation
- Initialize a React project using Vite in `C:\Users\NEVYA\.gemini\antigravity\scratch\react-meme-generator`.
- Install and configure Tailwind CSS (PostCSS, autoprefixer, and `tailwind.config.js`).

### Components (Built with Tailwind)
- **Header**: Clean, modern top navigation/title area.
- **MemeEditor**: The central canvas area displaying the selected template and overlaid text.
- **ControlsPanel**: A stylish side or bottom panel with input fields for customizing text and buttons to generate new templates or download.
- **TemplateGallery**: A responsive, auto-fitting grid of popular meme templates fetched from the Imgflip API.

### App Logic
- Fetch meme templates from the free Imgflip API (`https://api.imgflip.com/get_memes`).
- Manage state using React hooks (`useState`, `useEffect`).
- Use the `html-to-image` npm package to capture the meme component and allow users to download it.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
- Run the local Vite development server (`npm run dev`).
- Verify the UI looks premium, dynamic, and fully responsive across devices using Tailwind's utility classes.
- Test text inputs to ensure the meme image updates live.
- Test the "Download" button to verify it saves a proper image file.
